<DOC><DOCNO> AP880504-0217 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-04-88 2126EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--CouncilArrested     05-04 0148</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Council Arrested,0150</SECOND><HEAD>Entire City Council Arrested</HEAD><DATELINE>SPEZZANO DELLA SILA, Italy (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The mayor and the five-membercity council of this southern town were put under house arrestWednesday after being charged with embezzlement and fraud, policesaid.   The politicians, all Communists, were accused of using publicfunds totaling hundreds of thousands of dollars for privatepurposes from 1985 to 1987, according to authorities in Cosenza,the provincial capital.   Charged were Mayor Fernando Fabiano, 33, a doctor, andcouncilmen Francesco Curcio, 32; Francesco Abbritti, 31; FrancescoMancuso, 51; Emilio Carravetta, 39, and Biagio Martino, 47.   A spokesman for the Communist party in Cosenza was quoted by theItalian news agency ANSA as saying that ``further investigationwill prove the groundlessness of charges.''   The Italian Communist Party is the largest in Western Europe andhas campaigned vigorously against corruption in publicadministration, especially in the underdeveloped south.</TEXT></DOC>